The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Teachers to retire at 65

 New Delhi, March 15 

 (PTI): The government today decided to raise the 

 retirement age of teachers in centrally-funded institutions 

 from 62 to 65 years.

 Information and broadcasting minister Priya Ranjan Das Munshi said the move, approved at a cabinet meeting chaired by Prime Minister Manmohan Singh, was aimed at overcoming faculty shortage in institutes of higher learning.

 The cabinets decision for enhancing the age of retirement of faculty members in all centrally-funded educational institutions will help retain retiring faculty members with a view to meet the shortage of faculty, he said.

 The cabinet also approved a provision for re-employment beyond 65 years and up to 70 years against sanctioned vacancies, if these were not filled by regular candidates after screening under the UGCs guidelines, the minister said. 




